            <div type="page" facs="https://mangadex.org/chapter/1f0dd1b2-50d7-43bf-8721-b35c6685c55c/1" xml:id="pg_1">
                <cbml:panel n="1">
                    <cbml:balloon type="speech" who="Gyro Zeppeli">
                        <p>Don't ever speak to me ever again-ever</p>
                    </cbml:balloon>
                    <note>Gyro Zeppeli is in the corner saying something</note>
                </cbml:panel>
            </div>
            <div type="page" facs="https://mangadex.org/chapter/1f0dd1b2-50d7-43bf-8721-b35c6685c55c/2" xml:id="pg_2">
                <cbml:panel n="1">
                    <cbml:caption type="speech" who="Narrator">
                        <p>In 1191 A.D., 5 meters under the yard of Galstonbury Monastry, in Southwest Europe...</p>
                    </cbml:caption>
                    <cbml:caption type="speech" who="Narrator">
                        <p>An 'Old Map' written on parchment was discovered.</p>
                    </cbml:caption>
                    <note>Two archiologist find a treasure chest.</note>
                </cbml:panel>
                <cbml:panel n="2">
                    <cbml:caption type="speech" who="Narrator">
                        <p>It was a relic of 'Joseph of Arimathea'</p>
                        <note>In the chest is the 'Old Map.'</note>
                    </cbml:caption>
                </cbml:panel>
                <cbml:panel n="3">
                    <cbml:caption type="speech" who="Narrator">
                        <p>'Joseph of Arimathea' was the Saint, who, during the era of the Roman Empire.</p>
                    </cbml:caption>
                    <cbml:caption type="speech" who="Narrator">
                        <p>Brought the dead body of Jesus Christ down from the cross after he was crucified on the hill of Golgotha..</p>
                    </cbml:caption>
                    <cbml:caption type="speech" who="Narrator">
                        <p>..And who cleaned the body before its burial.</p>
                    </cbml:caption>
                    <note>Jesus is taken off the cross by Joseph. Joseph and Jesus's mother, Mary, holds him. Mary give him a kiss on the head.</note>
                </cbml:panel>
            </div>
